; Regression test for issue #566:
; Y/year directive not compatible with --input-date-format
;
; When --input-date-format is specified, separator conversion is disabled
; (dashes and dots are no longer converted to slashes before parsing).
; The short-form date %m-%d must still be recognized as a built-in format
; so that transactions using the Y directive with dash-separated dates work.

Y2014

04-21 * Test
    Assets:A        10.00 EUR
    Assets:B

test bal --input-date-format %Y-%m-%d
                   0  Assets
           10.00 EUR    A
          -10.00 EUR    B
--------------------
                   0
end test
